 (PLL)\nthat constitutes the point of entry for auditory phase locking and hence\nconserves the signal coherence. It provides an anchor for a dual coherent and\nnoncoherent auditory detection in the auditory brain that culminates in\nauditory accommodation. Implications on hearing impairments are discussed as\nwell.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Nov 2021 08:54:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 9 Nov 2021 08:18:51 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 12 Nov 2021 18:46:39 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 18 Apr 2022 17:00:58 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 24 May 2022 02:57:24 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 10 May 2023 21:33:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-12"}
